  "url": "https://www.lankadeepa.lk/news/\u0daf\u0dd9\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dd2-\u0db4\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dba\u0dda-\u0d89\u0daf\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7-\u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1-\u0d87\u0db8\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca/101-615686",
  "time_ut": 1656654915,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0dd9\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dd2 \u0db4\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dba\u0dda \u0d89\u0daf\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0d87\u0db8\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "From the minister of fuel to build the second terminal",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Oil bunkerers in this country have agreed to supply fuel to the Japanese company that is working on the construction of the second terminal in Katunayake.",
        "The warehouses have agreed to supply fuel following a special request made by Ports, Shipping and Aviation Minister Nimal Siripala de Silva.",
        "Japan's Taisei Corporation, which is engaged in the construction of the second terminal of Katunayake Airport, is facing the crisis of obtaining fuel, so the construction work has been slow for some time.",
        "Sumio Takahashi, Senior Administrative Manager, Taisei, told the Minister that he needed 13,000 liters of fuel per day.",
        "Commenting on this, the Minister of Ports, Shipping and Aviation Services Mr. Nimal Siripala de Silva stated that he had recently discussed with the Japanese Ambassador to Sri Lanka about the serious delay in the construction of the terminal due to the Corona epidemic and the current fuel crisis.",
        "The minister also said that he would like to express his thanks and gratitude to the fuel stockists in Sri Lanka who promised to supply fuel.",
        "Accordingly, the minister requested the representatives of the Japanese company to take necessary steps to complete the construction of the second terminal as soon as possible.",
        "Secretary to the Ministry KD H Ruwan Chandra, Chairman, Airport and Aviation Retired Major General GA Chandrasiri, representatives of Taisei Corporation of Japan and representatives of local IOC warehousing companies including IOC."
      ],
